cs.GT, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with game theory and incentives in protocols, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Game Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of local tables and virtual rewards also suggests a potential connection to distributed computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Distributed Systems) possible categories. Finally, the paper uses mathematical analysis and proofs to establish its results, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category.
